{"title_page": "William Levy (actor)", "text_new": "{{short description|American actor and model}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2011}}\n{{Spanish name|Guti\u00e9rrez|Levy}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = William Levy\n| image              = William Levy in 2015 (2).jpg\n| caption            = Levy in 2015\n| birth_name         = William Guti\u00e9rrez Levy<ref name=bio />\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1980|8|29|mf=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Cojimar]], [[Havana]], [[Cuba]]\n| residence          = [[Miami, Florida]], [[Santa Barbara, California]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Actor, model\n| years_active       = 2003\u2013present\n| partner            = [[Elizabeth Guti\u00e9rrez]] (2003\u20132019)\n| children           = 2\n| website            = {{URL|http://www.william-levy.net/|www.williamlevy.net}}\n}}\n'''William Guti\u00e9rrez Levy''' (born August 29, 1980),<ref name=bio>{{cite news|url=http://www2.esmas.com/entretenimiento/biografias/009295/william-levy|title=William Levy biography|publisher=[[Esmas.com|Esmas]]|language=Spanish}}</ref> known professionally as '''William Levy''', is a [[Cuban Americans|Cuban-American]] actor and former model.\n\n== Early life and education ==\nLevy was born in [[Cojimar]], [[Cuba]].<ref name=bio /> His maternal grandfather was Jewish (the origin of his surname, Levy),<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://nypost.com/2012/03/28/nobody-doesnt-like-william-levy/|title=Nobody doesn\u2019t like William Levy|last=Starr|first=Michael|date=March 28, 2012|work=[[New York Post]]|accessdate=June 22, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.interfaithfamily.com/arts_and_entertainment/popular_culture/interfaith_celebrities_dancing_and_more_witch_ancestry/|title=Interfaith Celebrities: Dancing and More Witch Ancestry|accessdate=June 22, 2018|date=March 20, 2012|last=Bloom|first=Nate|work=InterfaithFamily.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.oem.com.mx/esto/notas/n545359.htm|title=William Levy|publisher=Organizacion Editorial Mexicana|work=www.oem.com.mx|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last=Shira |first=Dahvi |url=https://people.com/tv/dancing-with-the-stars-cast-william-levy-5-things/ |title=Dancing with the Stars Cast: William Levy - 5 Things |magazine=People.com |date=February 28, 2012|accessdate=June 22, 2018}}</ref> although he grew up in a non-religious household.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/religion-backgrounds-latino-celebrities#7|title=Religious Backgrounds of Latino & Latina Hollywood Celebrities|website=www.latina.com|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref> Raised by his single mother, Barbara,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.starpulse.com/news/Kevin_Blair/2012/04/15/william_levy_talks_fleeing_cuba_findin |title=William Levy Talks Fleeing Cuba, Finding Instant Fame & 'Dancing With The Stars' |publisher=Starpulse.com |date=2012-04-15 |accessdate=2012-09-09}}</ref> Levy and his family, including his brother Jonathan Gutierrez Levy and sister Barbara Gutierrez Levy, immigrated to Miami, Florida when he was 20. He attended Barbara Goleman Senior high school, located in the suburb of [[Miami Lakes, Florida|Miami Lakes]]. After attending high school, he studied business administration on a baseball scholarship at [[St. Thomas University (Florida)|St. Thomas University]] for two years. He later went to Los Angeles to study acting, and continued his acting studies in Miami and Mexico City.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.so.com.mx/oncover.html |title=William Levy interview |publisher=Revista SO |work=www.so.com.mx |language=Spanish |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090831045825/http://www.so.com.mx/oncover.html |archivedate=August 31, 2009 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.reinarojas.com/william.html|title=William Levy|publisher=Reina Rojas |work=www.reinarojas.com |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nLevy worked as a model for the Next Models agency, and was featured in two reality shows broadcast by [[Telemundo]]: ''Isla de la Tentaci\u00f3n'' and ''Protagonistas de Novela 2''.<ref>[http://www.terra.com/protagonistas/novela2003/protagonistas.html ''Protagonistas de novela 2''] March 2009.</ref> In 2005 he performed at the Centro de Bellas Artes in [[San Juan, Puerto Rico]], starring in the play ''La Nena Tiene Tumbao''.\n\nHis debut on the Spanish-language channel [[Univision]] was in the [[Venevision International]] production of ''[[Olvidarte Jam\u00e1s]]''. He later appeared in ''[[Mi Vida Eres Tu]]'' and ''[[Acorralada]]''. In 2008, he appeared in his first film, ''Retazos de Vida'', directed by Viviana Cordero. He was invited by television producer [[Carla Estrada]] to star in ''[[Pasi\u00f3n (telenovela)|Pasi\u00f3n]]'', his breakthrough in Mexican telenovelas. [[Televisa]] cast him as the lead in ''[[Cuidado con el Angel]]'' with actress and ex-[[RBD]] singer [[Maite Perroni]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.esmas.com/cuidado-con-el-angel/ |title='&#39;esmas.com'&#39; |publisher=.esmas.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-27}}</ref> The show was first broadcast in Mexico in June 2008, and began airing in the United States in September 2008 on [[Univision]]. It averaged 5 million viewers per evening.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20250808_2,00.html |title='&#39;EW on the set of CCEA'&#39; |magazine=Entertainment Weekly |accessdate=2013-08-27}}</ref>\n\nLevy starred alongside [[Jacqueline Bracamontes]] on ''[[Sortilegio]]'' in 2009<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.esmas.com/entretenimiento/telenovelas/048051/william-levy-y-jackie-bracamontes-juntos-telenovela-carla-estrada |title='&#39;esmas.com'&#39; |publisher=.esmas.com |date=2009-03-12 |accessdate=2013-08-27}}</ref> ''Sortilegio'' aired on Univision, and the finale drew 6.6 million viewers, beating ABC and CBS for viewers in that time slot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/02/18/univision-beats-abc-and-cbs-wednesday-night-sortilegio-finale-draws-6-6-million/42386 |title='&#39;bythenumbers'&#39; |publisher=Tvbythenumbers.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-27}}</ref> In November 2009, the actor lent his voice to the Spanish version of the animated movie ''[[Planet 51]]''.<ref>[http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/notas/634611.html El Universal \"William Levy incursiona en el doblaje en la cinta Planet 51\"] - October 2009</ref> The movie opened on November 27 in Mexico and won an award for best animated Spanish-language film of 2009 ([[Premios Goya]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elmundo.es/especiales/premios_goya/2010/candidatos.html |title='&#39;El Mundo, Espa\u00f1a'&#39; |publisher=Elmundo.es |date= |accessdate=2013-08-27}}</ref> From November 2009 to February 2010, Levy toured several Mexican cities with the play ''Un Amante a la Medida'',<ref name=\"people2009\">[http://www.peopleenespanol.com/pespanol/articles/0,22490,1932692,00.html People en espa\u00f1ol \"William Levy en Un amante a la medida\"] - October 2009</ref> which toured in the United States in June 2010.\n\nLevy participated in the Mexican telenovela ''[[Triunfo del Amor (telenovela)|Triunfo del Amor]]'', a remake of the Venezuelan classic ''Cristal'', again with Maite Perroni. The telenovela aired on October 25, 2010, in El Canal de las Estrellas. Pedro Torres, executive producer of [[Mujeres Asesinas (Mexico)|Mujeres Asesinas]], confirmed Levy's role in the third season of the popular Mexican series. Levy starred as [[Jennifer Lopez]]'s love interest in the music video \"[[I'm Into You]]\", from her album ''[[Love? (album)|Love?]]''. It aired on NBC's [[Today (U.S. TV program)|Today]] on May 2, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hola.com/musica/2011041952177/jennifer-lopez-william-levy-videoclip/1/|title=Jennifer L\u00f3pez, muy sensual junto al nuevo gal\u00e1n de su videoclip, el modelo cubano William Levy|date=April 19, 2011|publisher=[[\u00a1Hola!]]|accessdate=April 19, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gossipcop.com/jennifer-lopez-today-show-may-2-2011-interview-video-im-into-you-premiere/|title=Jennifer Lopez Premieres 'I\u2019m Into You' |date=May 2, 2011|work=Gossip Cop |accessdate=May 8, 2011}}</ref> Levy appeared on the cover of ''[[People en Espa\u00f1ol]]'' for its special issue on the sexiest men of the year for 2011.<ref name=\"sexiestmen\">{{cite news| url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2011/08/25/william-levy-tops-people-en-espanol-list-sexiest-men/ | work=Fox News | title=William Levy tops People en Espa\u00f1ol list of sexiest men | date=August 25, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2012, it was announced that Levy would appear in two episodes of the VH1 television series ''[[Single Ladies (TV series)|Single Ladies]]'', with [[Denise Vasi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/tv/william-levy-guest-star-single-ladies |title=William Levy to Guest Star on 'Single Ladies' |work=Latina |first=Adriana |last=Rivera |date=January 4, 2012 |accessdate=February 29, 2012}}</ref> He was a participant in the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 14)|14th season]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'', with two-time mirror ball champion [[Cheryl Burke]] as his dance-pro partner; they finished in third place.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/dancing-with-the-stars/cast-announcement/ThemeGallery/934511 |title=Meet the Season 15 cast of Dancing with the Stars &#124; ABC TV Show News, Cast, Photos & More \u2013 ABC.com |publisher=Abc.go.com |date= |accessdate=2012-09-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realitytvworld.com/news/dancing-with-stars-crowns-donald-driver-and-peta-murgatroyd-new-champs--13503.php |title='Dancing with the Stars' crowns Donald Driver and Peta Murgatroyd new champs |publisher=Reality TV World |date=2012-05-23 |accessdate=2012-09-09}}</ref> In December 2012 Levy was cast as Captain Damian Fabre for the remake of ''[[La Tormenta]]'' titled ''[[La tempestad|La Tempestad]]'' which aired in 2013. Levy is set to star in ''Addicted'' an [[erotic]] [[drama]] based on the novel of the same name by [[Zane (author)|Zane]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/erotic-drama-addicted-rounds-cast-386129 |title=Erotic Drama 'Addicted' Rounds Out Cast |magazine=The Hollywood Reporter |date= November 2, 2012|accessdate=2013-08-27 |first=Borys |last=Kit}}</ref> [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] named Levy one of the Top 10 Latino Actors and Actresses in Hollywood.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/gallery/top-10-latino-actors-and-actresses/#!18/9-william-levy/|title=Top 10 Latino Actors and Actresses|magazine=Variety|accessdate=2015-04-15}}</ref>\n\nLevy co-starred in [[Tyler Perry]]'s film ''[[The Single Moms Club]]'' (2014).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/films.php?id=95984 |title=Tyler Perry's Single Mom's Club Trailer, News, Videos, and Reviews |publisher=ComingSoon.net |date= |accessdate=2013-08-27}}</ref> Levy was cast in the lead role as Warrior in the [[Brent Ryan Green]] film ''[[The Veil (2017 film)|The Veil]]'' (2017).<ref name=\"Screen International\">{{cite news|url= http://www.screendaily.com/news/production/the-veil-to-star-william-levy/5064378.article|title= The Veil to star William Levy |date= 5 December 2013 |accessdate= 8 August 2014 |magazine= Screen International}}</ref> In 2018, he began his role as Mateo Ferrera in the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] musical drama series ''[[Star (TV series)|Star]]''.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/star-william-levy-fox-drama-series-regular-season-3-1202447188/|title= \u2018Star\u2019: William Levy Joins Fox Drama As New Series Regular In Season 3 |date= 17 August 2018 |accessdate= 21 April 2019 |work= Deadline}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nLevy has been in an on-off relationship with Mexican-American actress [[Elizabeth Guti\u00e9rrez]] since 2003, and they have two children together, a son, Christopher Alexander, in 2006, and a daughter, Kailey Alexandra, on March 6, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvynovelas.com/us/noticias/17/08/29/elizabeth-gutierrez-sorprende-a-william-levy-en-su-cumpleanos/|title=Elizabeth Gutierrez sorprende a William Levy en su cumplea\u00f1os|publisher=TVyNovelas|language=Spanish|date=August 29, 2017|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.peopleenespanol.com/pespanol/articles/0,22490,2056542,00.html|title=William Levy y Elizabeth Guti\u00e9rrez por primera vez en familia|date=March 2, 2011|magazine=[[People en Espa\u00f1ol]]|accessdate=March 14, 2011}}</ref> On July 11, 2009, Levy converted to Catholicism.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{cite magazine|title=William Levy convertes to Catholicism|magazine=[[People en Espa\u00f1ol]]|date=July 14, 2009|url=http://www.peopleenespanol.com/pespanol/articles/0,22490,1910347,00.html|accessdate=October 19, 2010|quote=William Levy se convirti\u00f3 a la religi\u00f3n cat\u00f3lica|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Notimex|first=Domingo|title=William Levy was baptized and confirmed|pages=|publisher=Qui\u00e9n.com|date=July 12, 2009|url=http://www.quien.com/espectaculos/2009/07/12/william-levy-fue-bautizado-y-confirmado|accessdate=October 20, 2010|quote=William Levy fue bautizado y confirmado|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n=== Name change ===\nHe was born as William Guti\u00e9rrez Levy. He got the idea for his name change from a friend of his parents who tried helping the family get out of Cuba while William\u2019s mother was still pregnant, as he told ''Entertainment Tonight''. Levy is his mother\u2019s Jewish last name.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/06/13/7-things-william-levy_n_3435987.html|title=7 Things You Didn't Know About William Levy|last=VOXXI|date=2013-06-13|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2018-10-22|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Activism ==\nWilliam Levy is a philanthropist and donates his time to fix houses for low income families in Mexico as part of the \u201cAlianzas que Construyen\u201d [[Televisa|Televisa Foundation]].\n\n== ''Dancing with the Stars'' performances ==\nLevy was announced to be a contestant on ABC's ''Dancing With The Stars'' partnering with two-time champion [[Cheryl Burke]] for [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 14)|season 14]].\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#ccc;\"|Week #\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#ccc;\"|Dance/Song\n! colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#ccc;\"|Judges' score\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#ccc;\"|Result\n|- style=\"background:#ccc;\"\n| style=\"width:10%;\"|Inaba\n| style=\"width:10%;\"|Goodman\n| style=\"width:10%;\"|Tonioli\n|-\n|1\n|[[Cha-cha-cha (dance)|Cha-Cha-Cha]]/ \"[[International Love]]\"\n|8\n|8\n|8\n|No Elimination\n|-\n|2\n|[[Quickstep]]/ \"[[Nice Work If You Can Get It (song)|Nice Work If You Can Get It]]\"\n|9\n|7\n|9\n|Safe\n|-\n|3\n|[[Salsa (dance)|Salsa]]/ \"La Vida es un Carnaval\"\n|9\n|9\n|10\n|Safe\n|-\n|4\n|[[Jive (dance)|Jive]]/ \"[[We're Not Gonna Take It (Twisted Sister song)|We're Not Gonna Take It]]\"\n|7\n|7\n|8\n|Safe\n|-\n|5\n|[[Argentine Tango]]/ \"[[Buttons (The Pussycat Dolls song)|Buttons]]\"\n|10\n|9\n|10\n|Safe\n|-\n|6\n|[[Rhumba|Rumba]]/ \"[[Being with You (song)|Being with You]]\" <br> [[Motown|Motown Marathon]]\n|9 <br> Awarded\n|8 <br> 9\n|10 <br> Points\n|Safe\n|-\n|7\n|[[Viennese Waltz]]/ \"[[Ave Maria (Schubert)|Ave Maria]]\" <br> Team [[Paso Doble]]/ \"[[O Fortuna]]\"\n|9 <br> 9\n|9 <br> 8\n|9 <br> 9\n|Safe\n|-\n|8\n|[[Foxtrot]]/ \"[[Stray Cat Strut]]\" <br> [[Paso Doble]] (Trio Challenge)/ \"[[Diablo Rojo]]\"\n|10 <br> 9\n|10 <br> 9\n|10 <br> 9\n|Safe\n|-\n|9 <br> <small>Semi-finals</small>\n|[[Tango (dance)|Tango]]/ \"[[Sweet Dreams (Are Made of This)]]\" <br> [[Samba]]/ \"Magalenha\"\n|9 <br> 10\n|9 <br> 10\n|10 <br> 10\n|Safe\n|-\n|10 <br> <small>Finals</small>\n|[[Cha-cha-cha (dance)|Cha-Cha-Cha]]/ \"[[Raise Your Glass]]\" <br> [[Freestyle music|Freestyle]]/ \"[[Objection (Tango)]]\" <br> [[Salsa (dance)|Salsa]] (24-hour Challenge)/ Juventud de Presente\n|10 <br> 10 <br> 10\n|10 <br> 9 <br> 10\n|10 <br> 10 <br> 10\n|'''Third Place'''\n|}{{Clear}}\n\n== Filmography ==\n[[File:William Levy in 2015 (3).jpg|210px|thumb|right|Levy in 2015]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Film\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Planet 51]]''\n| Captain Charles \"Chuck\" Baker\n| Voice role\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[The Single Moms Club]]''\n| Manny\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Addicted (2014 film)|Addicted]]''\n| Quinton Canosa\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Term Life]]''\n| Alejandro\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Resident Evil: The Final Chapter]]''\n| Christian\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[A Change of Heart (film)|A Change of Heart]]''\n| Carlos\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[The Veil (2017 film)|The Veil]]''\n| Warrior\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Girls Trip]]''\n| Himself\n| Cameo\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Cinderelo''\n| Brando\n| \n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[El fantasma de mi novia]]''<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mabry|first1=Alexander|title=William Levy y Carmen Villalobos: detr\u00e1s de c\u00e1maras de El fantasma de mi novia|url=http://peopleenespanol.com/celebridades/william-levy-y-carmen-villalobos-detras-de-camaras-de-el-fantasma-de-mi-novia/#tras-bambalinas|website=peopleenespanol.com|publisher=[[People en Espa\u00f1ol]]|accessdate=7 May 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n| Chepa\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Television\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Mi vida eres t\u00fa]]''\n| Federico\n| \n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Olvidarte jam\u00e1s]]''\n| Germ\u00e1n Torres\n| \n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Acorralada]]''\n| Larry Ir\u00e1zabal\n| \n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Pasi\u00f3n (TV series)|Pasi\u00f3n]]''\n| Vasco Dari\u00e9n\n| \n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Plaza S\u00e9samo]]''\n| Himself\n| Episode: \"El problem\u00f3n\"\n|-\n| 2008\u20132009\n| ''[[Cuidado con el \u00e1ngel]]''\n| Juan Miguel\n| 194 episodes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Sortilegio]]''\n| Alejandro Lombardo\n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Mujeres asesinas (Mexican TV series)|Mujeres asesinas]]''\n| Fonsi / Conde Alfonso de Jes\u00fas Ruiz Machado y Ortigoza\n| Episode: \"Annette y Ana, Nobles\"\n|-\n| 2010-2011\n| ''[[Triunfo del amor]]''\n| Maximiliano Sandoval\n| 175 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]''\n| Himself\n| Contestant\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Single Ladies (TV series)|Single Ladies]]''\n| Antonio\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[La Tempestad]]''\n| Dami\u00e1n Fabr\u00e9\n| 119 episodes\n|-\n| 2018-2019\n| ''[[Star (TV series)|Star]]''\n| Mateo\n| Main role\n|}\n\n== Theater ==\n* ''Un amante a la medida'' (2009\u201310)\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n=== Premios Bravo ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"85%\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\"| Year\n! width=\"40%\"| Category\n! width=\"30%\"| Work\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|- style=\"text-align: center; top\"\n| 2008\n| Best Newcomer<ref>[http://www.elporvenir.com.mx/notas.asp?nota_id=257609 El Porvenir \"William Levy gana el premio Bravo como actor revelaci\u00f3n por su papel en telenovela Pasi\u00f3n\"]</ref>\n| ''[[Pasi\u00f3n (telenovela)|Pasi\u00f3n]]''\n| {{won}}\n|- style=\"text-align: center; top\"\n| 2010\n| Best Actor<ref>[http://www.oem.com.mx/esto/notas/n1806641.htm OEM \"Gran fiesta de los premios Bravo -William Levy premiado\"]</ref>\n| ''[[Sortilegio]]''\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n=== [[Premios Juventud]] ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"85%\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\"| Year\n! width=\"40%\"| Category\n! width=\"30%\"| Work\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|- style=\"text-align: center; top\"\n| [[2009 Premios Juventud|2009]]\n|It's great!<ref>[http://www.univision.com/content/content.jhtml;jsessionid=LGAMUR5EGHT3SCWIAAOSFFQKZAAB2IWC?chid=6&schid=10416&secid=11221&cid=1599818 ''Univision'' Ganadores de Premio Juventud 2009]</ref>\n| ''[[Cuidado con el \u00e1ngel]]''\n| {{won}}\n|- style=\"text-align: center; top\"\n| [[2010 Premios Juventud|2010]]\n| It's great!<ref>[http://www.tvyespectaculos.com/2010/07/19/ganadores-premios-juventud-2010/ TVyEspect\u00e1culos \"William Levy ganador Premio Juventud al m\u00e1s gal\u00e1n]</ref>\n| ''[[Sortilegio]]''\n| {{won}}\n|- style=\"text-align: center; top\"\n| 2011\n| It's great!<ref>[http://musica.univision.com/premios-juventud/ganadores/openpage/2011-03-14/premios-juventud-2011-ganadores-novelas Ganadores Premios Juventud 2011]</ref>\n| ''[[Triunfo del amor]]''\n| {{won}}\n|- style=\"text-align: center; top\"\n| [[2014 Premios Juventud|2014]]\n| It's great!<ref>{{cite web |url=http://musica.univision.com/article/1945616/2014-05-07/premios-juventud/lo-ultimo/lista-completa-de-nominados-premios-juventud-2014 |title=Lista completa de nominados Premios Juventud 2014 |accessdate=May 19, 2014 |last= |first= |date=May 7, 2014 |language=Spanish }}</ref>\n| ''[[La Tempestad]]''\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n=== [[Premios TVyNovelas]] ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"85%\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\"| Year\n! width=\"40%\"| Category\n! width=\"30%\"| Work\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|- style=\"text-align: center; top\"\n|2010\n| Best Actor<ref>[http://www.tvyespectaculos.com/2010/02/08/nominados-a-los-premios-tvynovelas-2010/ TVyEspect\u00e1culos \"William Levy nominado al premio TV&Novelas como Mejor actor\"]</ref>\n| ''[[Sortilegio]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n=== Califa de oro ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"85%\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\"| Year\n! width=\"40%\"| Category\n! width=\"30%\"| Work\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|- style=\"text-align: center; top\"\n| 2012\n| Best Actor<ref>[http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/notas/799935.html El Universal \"William Levy recibir\u00e1 el Califa de Oro\"]</ref>\n| ''[[Triunfo del amor]]''\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n=== Premios Casandra ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"85%\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\"| Year\n! width=\"40%\"| Category\n! width=\"30%\"| Work\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|- style=\"text-align: center; top\"\n| 2012\n| Revelation Image<ref>[http://www.delazonaoriental.net/ DelaZonaOriental.net \"El actor William Levy ser\u00e1 galardonado con u